1
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:18,750
[MABU]
I'm so hot. Isn't this enough?

2
00:00:18,833 --> 00:00:20,750
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
"Otter" nonsense.

3
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:23,500
It's far too early to pull out.

4
00:00:23,583 --> 00:00:26,416
[MABU]
But I... I can't take any more.

5
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,875
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
"Otterly" pathetic.

6
00:00:28,958 --> 00:00:31,625
Your endurance really
could use some work.

7
00:00:33,125 --> 00:00:36,125
[MABU]
Please, stop teasing me.

8
00:00:36,208 --> 00:00:40,250
[IMPERIAL BOSS] If you insist,
then pull it out yourself.

9
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:42,416
-[clattering]
-[gasps]

10
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,625
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
You "otter" know better.

11
00:00:44,708 --> 00:00:46,833
Look at how doughy they are.

12
00:00:46,916 --> 00:00:49,083
Too soon. Too soon.

13
00:00:49,166 --> 00:00:52,125
-May we please try it again?
-[IMPERIAL BOSS] Later.

14
00:00:52,208 --> 00:00:55,750
But first,
some fine-tuning is in "otter."

15
00:00:55,833 --> 00:01:00,000
Why don't you go lay down
and show me what's inside you?

16
00:01:00,083 --> 00:01:01,750
As you wish.

17
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:04,625
I only want to be desired again.

18
00:01:04,708 --> 00:01:06,625
Whatever it takes,
I'll do it.

19
00:01:06,708 --> 00:01:08,333
[gasps]

20
00:01:08,416 --> 00:01:10,875
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Mabu, my beautiful doll.

21
00:01:10,958 --> 00:01:13,958
I pity you, like no "otter."

22
00:02:44,375 --> 00:02:47,625
[SARA]
Good morning to you!

23
00:02:47,708 --> 00:02:49,958
Sara Azuma here.

24
00:02:50,041 --> 00:02:54,250
And with my lucky selfies,
you'll be happy every day!

25
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:57,541
We have a summer break special
on the plate for today!

26
00:02:57,625 --> 00:03:00,250
I'm going to rank all our
previous lucky selfie items

27
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:02,958
in an extremely biased,
no-holds-barred

28
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:04,208
elimination match,

29
00:03:04,291 --> 00:03:06,083
where I alone am judge and jury!

30
00:03:06,166 --> 00:03:09,458
[REO] Now that's a balanced
breakfast if I've ever seen one.

31
00:03:09,541 --> 00:03:10,958
Let's dig in!

32
00:03:11,041 --> 00:03:13,208
That I shall.

33
00:03:13,291 --> 00:03:15,708
[REO]
I didn't mean you!

34
00:03:16,791 --> 00:03:19,791
What's the point
in playing this game?

35
00:03:19,875 --> 00:03:21,208
You'll just get sick.

36
00:03:21,291 --> 00:03:23,458
I can actually eat food now.

37
00:03:23,541 --> 00:03:25,250
Thanks to my last maintenance.

38
00:03:26,291 --> 00:03:28,375
Is that so?

39
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:30,333
You think if you eat
your old favorites,

40
00:03:30,416 --> 00:03:31,958
everything'll be back to normal?

41
00:03:32,041 --> 00:03:33,625
That I'll accept you?

42
00:03:33,708 --> 00:03:36,916
All you're doing here
is playing pretend.

43
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,875
Well, don't bother,
because it's a waste of time.

44
00:03:39,958 --> 00:03:42,666
I know that everything about you
is a lie.

45
00:03:44,166 --> 00:03:47,250
It's not me
that I'm trying to make happy.

46
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:51,083
[scoffs] Yeah, yeah, you think
I wanna hear this crap?

47
00:03:52,416 --> 00:03:54,250
Reo.
Listen to me.

48
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:55,833
I don't care.

49
00:03:55,916 --> 00:03:57,208
By the way,

50
00:03:57,291 --> 00:03:59,291
that thing we saw is our secret.

51
00:03:59,375 --> 00:04:01,666
So don't spill it
to your little boyfriend

52
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:03,166
you're so eager to please.

53
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:05,625
-All right.
-[SARA] That's all!

54
00:04:05,708 --> 00:04:08,375
[BOTH]
The food was great, thank you!

55
00:04:13,083 --> 00:04:15,666
[HARUKA] Kazu,
I'm sorry it took so long,

56
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:18,625
but there's something important
I need to give you.

57
00:04:18,708 --> 00:04:21,166
She wanted me to bring it
to you that day.

58
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:24,291
Actually, could you
keep it for a while?

59
00:04:24,375 --> 00:04:26,541
Huh? I'm confused.

60
00:04:26,625 --> 00:04:29,041
[KAZUKI] For now,
I think it's more important

61
00:04:29,125 --> 00:04:30,500
to build connections
with the people

62
00:04:30,583 --> 00:04:32,041
who are already close to me.

63
00:04:32,125 --> 00:04:34,750
You mean,
people close to you like me?

64
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:37,125
And like Mom and Dad, too,
maybe?

65
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:40,541
[laughs]

66
00:04:40,625 --> 00:04:42,458
Yeah, definitely!

67
00:04:42,541 --> 00:04:45,458
[laughs]
That's great!

68
00:04:45,541 --> 00:04:47,958
[munching]

69
00:04:48,041 --> 00:04:50,833
[OTONE]
This is it! Summer's here!

70
00:04:50,916 --> 00:04:52,875
Whether you laugh
or whether you cry,

71
00:04:52,958 --> 00:04:55,000
you're only gonna get one try!

72
00:04:55,083 --> 00:04:56,708
So no matter what you do,

73
00:04:56,791 --> 00:04:59,083
you've gotta give it
a hundred percent!

74
00:04:59,166 --> 00:05:00,458
Whoo!

75
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:02,833
Been a while. I might be rusty.

76
00:05:02,916 --> 00:05:05,750
-Is that okay?
-[ENTA] You're fine.

77
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:07,291
Did you let my sister know

78
00:05:07,375 --> 00:05:09,208
that you're planning on
coming back to the soccer club?

79
00:05:09,291 --> 00:05:10,666
Yep!

80
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:12,833
I'll be in at the start
of next semester.

81
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:14,000
All right!

82
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:15,541
We've got all summer to train!

83
00:05:15,625 --> 00:05:18,125
Let's get you back
in fighting shape, okay?

84
00:05:18,208 --> 00:05:20,666
Oh, uh, sorry!

85
00:05:25,416 --> 00:05:27,000
[KAZUKI]
Hey!

86
00:05:27,083 --> 00:05:28,125
Toi!

87
00:05:28,208 --> 00:05:30,000
Get down here!

88
00:05:30,083 --> 00:05:32,458
Why is he so happy?

89
00:05:32,541 --> 00:05:34,541
[KAZUKI]
Come play soccer with us!

90
00:05:35,541 --> 00:05:36,833
I see.

91
00:05:36,916 --> 00:05:38,916
I guess he picked it
back up again.

92
00:05:40,291 --> 00:05:41,708
[grunts]

93
00:05:41,791 --> 00:05:43,333
Whoa.

94
00:05:43,416 --> 00:05:45,916
-Did you used to play, too?
-Uh-huh.

95
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,875
Well, I mean, kinda.

96
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:51,625
You're way better
than just "kinda!" Aw, man!

97
00:05:51,708 --> 00:05:53,958
You gotta play on the team
with us!

98
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:56,625
I mean, how fun would that be?

99
00:05:56,708 --> 00:05:59,208
And we already know
our teamwork's solid, right?

100
00:05:59,291 --> 00:06:00,750
Well?
Tell him!

101
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:02,250
This is great!

102
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:04,291
Kuji, if you're on the team
with us,

103
00:06:04,375 --> 00:06:05,833
we might even make nationals!

104
00:06:05,916 --> 00:06:07,666
Oh, uh, I don't know.

105
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:09,916
Huh? You don't want to?

106
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,250
It's not that.

107
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:13,166
I mean, I wouldn't mind, but--
Oh!

108
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:14,875
Would you give it up already?

109
00:06:14,958 --> 00:06:16,583
I can tell you're excited!

110
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:20,208
[yells]

111
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:22,875
-Your aim sucks!
-[TOI] Nope. Nailed it.

112
00:06:22,958 --> 00:06:24,958
[KAZUKI laughs]

113
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:35,833
[REO] If I get those dishes,
I can fix all this.

114
00:06:37,458 --> 00:06:39,416
[bubbling]

115
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,958
[gasps]

116
00:06:41,958 --> 00:06:44,000
Mabu!

117
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,375
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
So you're finally awake.

118
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:52,916
Who are you?

119
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,333
An otter, obviously.

120
00:06:55,416 --> 00:06:59,083
Specifically, I'm the Otter
Empire's Chief "Otticer"

121
00:06:59,166 --> 00:07:00,708
of Science and Technology.

122
00:07:00,791 --> 00:07:02,458
You were caught up
in an accident

123
00:07:02,541 --> 00:07:05,000
during the destruction
of the Kappa Kingdom.

124
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:06,458
Accident.

125
00:07:06,541 --> 00:07:08,875
Where's Mabu? Is he--

126
00:07:09,958 --> 00:07:12,750
I'm afraid he was
gravely injured.

127
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:15,583
We were able to retrieve him
from the rubble,

128
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:17,041
but it was too late.

129
00:07:17,125 --> 00:07:18,958
-[REO] No.
-[clattering]

130
00:07:19,041 --> 00:07:21,583
You can't die!
Do you hear me?

131
00:07:21,666 --> 00:07:24,791
Damn it, Mabu, I'm not letting
you leave this world without me!

132
00:07:24,875 --> 00:07:27,458
I'm right here!
This can't be true!

133
00:07:27,541 --> 00:07:29,791
[IMPERIAL BOSS] "Dis-otter-sty"
is not my policy.

134
00:07:29,875 --> 00:07:32,750
All is just as it appears.

135
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:35,041
But what if there was some way

136
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:37,000
that you could
save your partner?

137
00:07:37,083 --> 00:07:41,041
[REO] I would do anything
just to hear his voice again.

138
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:43,083
He's all I have.

139
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:57,041
[beeping]

140
00:08:03,791 --> 00:08:07,291
-[TOI] What happened?
-[KAZUKI] Who would do this?

141
00:08:07,375 --> 00:08:10,250
Some sicko, I bet.

142
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:12,666
What are you doing?

143
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:14,166
Isn't it obvious?

144
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:15,666
Cleaning up.

145
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:17,041
This is our spot.

146
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:18,541
You mean that?

147
00:08:18,625 --> 00:08:20,041
[KAZUKI]
Come on!

148
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,833
Let's do this together!

149
00:08:24,583 --> 00:08:26,958
♪

150
00:08:36,208 --> 00:08:38,958
♪

151
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,000
[KAZUKI]
Okay, see you tomorrow!

152
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:56,708
[ENTA, TOI]
Yeah.

153
00:08:56,791 --> 00:08:59,791
[MABU] I regret to inform you
that systems are operating

154
00:08:59,875 --> 00:09:01,666
at only thirty-nine percent.

155
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:03,208
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Surely not.

156
00:09:03,291 --> 00:09:05,833
[MABU] I would not jest about
such a serious matter.

157
00:09:05,916 --> 00:09:08,041
The kappa zombie reserves
are dwindling.

158
00:09:08,125 --> 00:09:09,458
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
I "otter" remind you,

159
00:09:09,541 --> 00:09:11,125
unless this is remedied,

160
00:09:11,208 --> 00:09:14,250
it puts the survival of you
and your partner in jeopardy.

161
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:16,333
I'll do everything
I can to fix this.

162
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:18,625
[IMPERIAL BOSS] Then let's hope
you can prove your loyalty

163
00:09:18,708 --> 00:09:22,416
to the empire without any hint
of "dis-otter-sty."

164
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:25,791
Now, do you have anything else
to report?

165
00:09:25,875 --> 00:09:27,583
[MABU]
No, sir.

166
00:09:27,666 --> 00:09:31,333
[KAZUKI] My life used to be
weighed down by secrets.

167
00:09:31,416 --> 00:09:33,791
Three rules that decided
everything for me.

168
00:09:33,875 --> 00:09:35,416
[SARA] With my lucky selfies,

169
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:38,250
you'll be happy
every single day!

170
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:41,375
[KAZUKI] I had to carry a box,
watch Sara,

171
00:09:41,458 --> 00:09:43,625
and take lucky selfies.

172
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:46,875
[SARA] Balls!
Like soccer balls!

173
00:09:46,958 --> 00:09:49,500
The more you get,
the happier you'll be!

174
00:09:49,583 --> 00:09:51,958
That's all we have
on the plate for now!

175
00:09:52,041 --> 00:09:54,416
Get Sara-cky!

176
00:09:57,166 --> 00:10:00,875
[KAZUKI] I'm free of that now,
but I still have a few secrets.

177
00:10:00,958 --> 00:10:03,375
Like turning into a kappa,
for example.

178
00:10:04,416 --> 00:10:05,916
[laughs]

179
00:10:09,041 --> 00:10:11,750
And sure, that's stressful.

180
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:14,333
But I have friends
I've connected with.

181
00:10:14,416 --> 00:10:17,208
We can make it through
anything together.

182
00:10:23,041 --> 00:10:25,500
-[TOI] Seriously?
-[ENTA] They did it again?

183
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:27,000
We just cleaned this!

184
00:10:27,083 --> 00:10:29,333
[TOI] Well, I guess
we pissed somebody off.

185
00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:31,958
[ENTA]
Huh? Who? Why?

186
00:10:32,041 --> 00:10:33,875
-[KAZUKI] It's fine.
-Kazuki?

187
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:35,875
Who says we can't
clean it again?

188
00:10:35,958 --> 00:10:38,791
Let's show these bullies
that we're not giving up.

189
00:10:38,875 --> 00:10:41,083
A little trash isn't
going to stop us!

190
00:10:41,166 --> 00:10:42,250
You're right.

191
00:10:42,333 --> 00:10:43,625
Let's do this!

192
00:10:43,708 --> 00:10:45,375
We'll go even faster this time!

193
00:10:45,458 --> 00:10:50,041
[phone ringing]

194
00:10:52,458 --> 00:10:56,000
[ENTA] Damn it!
It's not coming off!

195
00:10:56,083 --> 00:10:57,416
[KAZUKI]
Is something up?

196
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:59,166
You better hurry!

197
00:10:59,250 --> 00:11:01,541
You owe us croquettes
when we're done here!

198
00:11:01,625 --> 00:11:03,166
Sorry, guys.

199
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:05,291
[KAZUKI]
Huh? What is it?

200
00:11:05,375 --> 00:11:07,083
[TOI]
Something came up.

201
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:10,958
Turns out I can't play soccer
with you after all.

202
00:11:15,291 --> 00:11:17,833
[TOI] That call I just got
was from my brother.

203
00:11:17,916 --> 00:11:21,416
One of his jobs fell through.
A major one.

204
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:23,541
It wasn't exactly legal.

205
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:26,125
So there's always a big risk.

206
00:11:26,208 --> 00:11:28,666
This time, one of his partners
sold him out.

207
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:31,375
He's gonna be
a wanted man, soon.

208
00:11:31,458 --> 00:11:32,958
He can't stay in one place.

209
00:11:34,375 --> 00:11:38,416
When he skips town,
I'll be going with him.

210
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:39,916
And that's that.

211
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:43,333
Forget what I said
about the soccer club.

212
00:11:46,708 --> 00:11:48,791
-[KAZUKI] Just one more.
-Huh?

213
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:50,833
One more Dish of Hope!

214
00:11:50,916 --> 00:11:53,250
Then we'll have five
and make a wish!

215
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:55,916
And then we can use it
to help out your brother!

216
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,791
But Kazuki...

217
00:11:57,875 --> 00:12:01,208
[KAZUKI] If we do that, then you
won't have to leave anymore!

218
00:12:01,291 --> 00:12:03,041
Uh, yeah. I guess.

219
00:12:03,125 --> 00:12:04,666
Then that settles it!

220
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:06,333
Right? Easy!

221
00:12:06,416 --> 00:12:08,875
You bet!
One more silver plate!

222
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:10,791
We got your back on this, Kuji!

223
00:12:10,875 --> 00:12:13,416
You heard him!
Don't go anywhere!

224
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,000
We're a team!

225
00:12:15,083 --> 00:12:16,625
[ENTA]
Got that right!

226
00:12:18,125 --> 00:12:19,958
I guess you wouldn't know.

227
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:22,958
But this is the real Kazuki
you're seeing now.

228
00:12:23,041 --> 00:12:26,208
This is what he was like
before Haruka's accident.

229
00:12:26,291 --> 00:12:29,208
He finally got
his old smile back.

230
00:12:29,291 --> 00:12:32,000
I'd been waiting so long.
I was losing hope.

231
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:35,208
[TOI]
Are you cool with this?

232
00:12:35,291 --> 00:12:36,666
You said before.

233
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:38,250
You wanted to spend
the wish on him,

234
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:41,166
so I'm kinda imposing
on all of that, aren't I?

235
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:42,333
What's that?

236
00:12:42,416 --> 00:12:43,833
Kuji is worried about me?

237
00:12:43,916 --> 00:12:45,916
Why, up is down and down is up!

238
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,500
I'm serious!

239
00:12:47,583 --> 00:12:48,833
It's just a joke!

240
00:12:48,916 --> 00:12:50,541
I'm sorry.

241
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:54,416
But yeah, of course I still want
Kazuki's wishes to come true.

242
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:56,583
That's what I mean!

243
00:12:56,666 --> 00:13:00,208
But right now,
helping you is his wish.

244
00:13:00,291 --> 00:13:02,125
So it all works out fine!

245
00:13:02,208 --> 00:13:04,875
So just smile and say thank you.

246
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:08,208
-[TOI] Thank you.
-Nah.

247
00:13:08,291 --> 00:13:10,416
That's actually kinda gross.
No deal.

248
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:11,916
[TOI]
I'll gut your ass!

249
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,375
-[laughs]
-I'm all done!

250
00:13:13,458 --> 00:13:15,708
Let's go see Keppi, okay?

251
00:13:15,791 --> 00:13:18,708
Kero Force, march!

252
00:13:18,791 --> 00:13:22,916
Once again, we shall valiantly
right the wrongs of this city!

